book also contributes to this growing problem. The social media website knows what you’re interested in and presents to you links about those topics. Facebook knows what your interactions are, the things you’ve browsed, and content that will make you browse further. That’s why some people have taken advantage of this fact and post a lot of fake news to destabilize organizations, people, and even governments.</h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"Body\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-114\" src=\"http://static.noblebuzz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/The-Growing-Risk-of-Online-Fake-News_02.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"714\" height=\"400\" /></h4>\r\n<h4 class=\"Body\">So, be careful in reading and sharing what you see in your timeline. Make sure it’s real and not meant to create chaos. Otherwise, you’re just going to be part of the problem, and not the solution.</h4>','The Growing Risk of Online Fake News','','publish','closed','closed','','the-growing-risk-of-online-fake-news','','','2017-07-06 07:27:11','2017-07-06 07:27:11','',0,'http://static.noblebuzz.com/?p=112',0,'post','',0),(113,1,'2017-07-06 07:25:52','2017-07-06 07:25:52','','A man poses with a magnifier in front of a Facebook logo on display in this illustration taken in Sarajevo','A man poses with a magnifier in front of a Facebook logo on display in this illustration taken in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, December 16, 2015.   REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Illustration','inherit','closed','closed','','a-man-poses-with-a-magnifier-in-front-of-a-facebook-logo-on-display-in-this-illustration-taken-in-sarajevo','','','2017-07-06 07:25:52','2017-07-06 07:25:52','',112,'http://static.noblebuzz.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/The-Growing-Risk-of-Online-Fake-News_01.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(114,1,'2017-07-06 07:25:53','2017-07-06 07:25:53','','The Growing Risk of Online Fake News_02','','inherit','closed','closed','','the-growing-risk-of-online-fake-news_02','','','2017-07-06 07:25:53','2017-07-06 07:25:53','',112,'http://static.n